HEADWORD: Febrifuge
<hw>Feb"ri*fuge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>febris</ets> fever + <ets>fugare</ets> to put to flight, from
<ets>fugere</ets> to flee: cf. F. <ets>f⟦eacute⟧brifuge</ets>. see
<er>Febrile</er>, <er>Feverfew</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
medicine serving to mitigate or remove fever.</def> --
<def2><pos>a.</pos> <def>Antifebrile.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

